channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: 'Death to America': NYPD Stunned at Hateful Signs Found in NYU Pro-Hamas Camp
Dean Phillips becomes first House Democrat to call on Rep. Cuellar to resign after indictment
item.description: Rep. Dean Phillips was the first House Democrat to call on colleague Rep. Henry Cuellar, also a Democrat, to resign after his bribery and conspiracy indictment Friday.

item.title: Trump Slams 'Deranged' Special Counsel Over Foul-Up
item.description: Republican presumptive nominee Donald Trump seized on a mistake by special counsel Jack Smith's office on Friday, which admitted it mishandled classified documents that Trump stands accused of mishandling.

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: Storm Chaser Saves Family From a Texas Tornado, Transports Them to the Hospital
Border Patrol sector stops hundreds of Chinese illegal immigrants in just two days as numbers soar
item.description: The San Diego Border Patrol Sector has seen a surge in migrants from China, encountering more nationals in two days than the entire border did in FY 21.

item.title: Republicans Bash Philadelphia DA Over Crime, Policies
item.description: House Republicans blasted Philadelphia District Attorney Larry Krasner and his "pro-criminal policies" during a field hearing on Friday in Center City, Pennsylvania.

item.title: Fox News Politics: Mr. Broke It
item.description: The latest updates from the 2024 campaign trail, exclusive interviews and more Fox News politics content

item.title: Rep. Perry to Newsmax: 'People Who Hate America' Spur Protests
item.description: Rep. Scott Perry, R-Penn., said Friday that the protests on campuses of U.S. colleges and universities are "the result of bringing people that hate America to America."

item.title: Ted Cruz Wallops Marjorie Taylor Greene Over Effort to Oust Speaker Mike Johnson
Prosecutors repeatedly reference Trump’s Access Hollywood scandal after judge ruled tape itself 'prejudicial'
item.description: New York prosecutors continue to heavily reference the infamous leaked Access Hollywood tape capturing Trump's crude comments about women despite judge deeming the tape itself prejudicial.

item.title: DOJ Threatens to Sue Iowa if It Acts on Immigration Law
item.description: Iowa will face legal consequences if it enforces a recently passed immigration law that prohibits people from being in the state if they were previously denied entry into the United States, the Des Moines Register reported.

item.title: Columbia Prez Breaks Silence on NYPD's Raid on Pro-Hamas Mob, Statement Will Please Exactly No One
Nancy Pelosi, John Kerry, other Biden allies awarded Presidential Medal of Freedom
item.description: President Biden awarded 19 individuals with the United States' highest civilian award, the Presidential Medal of Freedom, on Friday — including many Democratic allies.

item.title: Sen. Vance Decries Biden Opening Obamacare to Migrants
item.description: Sen. J.D. Vance, R-Ohio, decried the actions of President Joe Biden on Friday, saying he is spending Americans' "hard-earned money" to cover the healthcare costs of illegal migrants.
